gep.model

Class Chromosome<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gep.model.Chromosome<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The return parameter type of the GeneElements contained in this Chromosomes genes. TODO allow various types within one Chromosome (e.g. UntypedChromosome as a subclass or the need to provide conversion functions).
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Chromosome<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class implements a Chromosome, which is basically a collection of modifiable and unmodifiable genes linked by a linking function.
    Author:
    Johannes Wortmann

        public Gene<T> getGene(int geneId)
        Returns the gene of this Chromosome corresponding to the given gene id. 
         GeneId: = 0 linking function, 
         > 0 normal gene (ascending) 
         < 0 immutable gene (ascending, after id negation)
